In the anthracite coal region of Eastern Pennsylvania, coal seam fires are common.
This fire, located under the Pennsylvania town of Centralia, periodically burned to the surface, emitting smoke and noxious fumes.
Here, smoke and fumes have killed all vegetation and started a forest fire (below).
