Since 1999, 28 watershed projects have been completed.
Surface subsidence resulted when the roof collapsed in an abandoned underground mine 150 feet below a residential area adjacent to a high school in Fairmont, West Virginia.
After drilling 320 boreholes, 2,000 cubic yards of concrete was pumped into the boreholes.
The resulting concrete pillars support the mine's roof and will prevent future subsidence.
Significant on-the-ground improvement has been made by watershed projects during 2002.
For example, the Mountain Watershed Association Sag amore Mine Drainage Project located in northeast Fayette County Figure 2 Pennsylvania.
