The internship prog ram enables college students (juniors and above) to bring technical expertise and youthful energ y to volunteer watershed org anizations.
Each intern spends a semester working in a watershed, and receives college credit for his or her efforts.
In 2002, the Office of Surface Mining funding provided a $2,000 stipend and $500 for project expenses to each intern.
In ever y case, the interns strengthened the capacity of the sponsoring watershed g roup, adding to their monitoring data, developing watershed plans, and building public awareness.
